caption.text:
I got universal in one ear saying we need FastX2 by March 2026!

I have Comcast in the other ear saying we need two movies to be the Finale!

Then the writer on Fast Five sent me this image and said we need to see DOM and HOBBS resolve their differences. 

I just want to get back to real street racing, practical stunts… and a reunion of that beautiful brotherhood. 

Happy Thanksgiving…

caption.text:
It was such an honor to be asked to narrate for American Valor in anticipation of Veterans Day.

So many thoughts… the first film I was ever paid for as an actor, who started at seven years old, was “Saving Private Ryan.” I was so proud to be a part of the retelling of WW2 from none other than Steven Spielberg. Funny story… earlier this year, as we were celebrating another good friend, Chris Nolan… I was talking to “Family First” Brian Roberts, when Steven came across the room yelling, “Vinnie, my godson, I am sorry for killing Carparzo off so early! And to make it up to you, I will co-direct Hannibal!”

How can you not love someone who started my career and wants to help me realize a lifelong dream of directing Hannibal Barca?

I want to say to the veterans of our world… I appreciate you, I applaud you, and I am grateful for the true heroism you have shown to keep our beautiful country alive. You soldiers are the true heroes.

Hmmm, co-direct with Steven...

Happy Veterans Day weekend!

caption.text:
Looking back, a quarter century ago… I believe this was the moment we knew that our brotherhood was going to change Hollywood, that you and I meant something to the world… a multicultural brotherhood, bond not by blood, but by love…

To think I just saw concept art for the next chapter. Brian… yeah, I will have to brace myself for this next film…

I saw your mother and Father this summer. I could feel you in their loving embrace… for the last 11 years I have held words like talismans of light, each have gifted me so much with their love and wisdom. 

And your daughter… my God, she’s actually continuing your good works, speaking on behalf of our oceans. Just weeks ago, at a birthday dinner… Meadow gave a toast, man you would have been so damn proud. She has a way of speaking from her heart that echos the melody of grace so beautifully. 

Traveling to the corners of the world…  there’s always someone there to remind me of the impact we’ve had on their lives. Either showing their cars with pride, haha… or simply saying, they feel like they were raised by us. That beautiful brotherhood, a quarter century old. 

A brotherhood, timeless and bond by love. For that I am eternally grateful… but damn, I miss you Pablo. 

Happy birthday…
